.TH HSH 1 "2021-03-01" "GNU" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
.B hsh - \fRcustom implementation of a linux and unix like shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B \f COMMAND \fI[ARGUMENTS]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B
\fRhsh executes COMMAND just like a standard shell application found in linux and unix systems. Implemented
using the c programming language

.SH COMMAND
.TB
.B ls \- \fRlist content of a directory. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.TB
.B cd \- \fRchange the current working directory. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.TB
.B mkdir \- \fRcreate a directory. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.TB
.B touch \- \fRlcreate a file. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.TB
.B rm \- \fRremove a file or directory. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.TB
.B which \- \fRfind the binary path of a command. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.TB
.B alias \- \fRcreate a alternative name of a command. [ARGUMENTS] arguments are just like a normal linux shell

.SH AUTHORS
.TB
.B \fRWritten and maintained by Bereket Abera \- bereket5042@gmail.com and Beniyam Legesse \- lbeniyam@gmail.com
